4. Speaker-diarization models (audio::speaker)

audio::speaker runs pyannote's segmentation net and the WeSpeaker embedder on
CoreML and feeds dia's community-1 PLDA clustering. Attribution obligations:

  - pyannote/speaker-diarization-community-1 (the PLDA dia clusters through):
    CC-BY-4.0 — REQUIRES attribution.
  - pyannote/segmentation-3.0 (both sources' segmenters derive from it): MIT.
  - WeSpeaker embedder (wenet-e2e/wespeaker): see its model license
    (https://github.com/wenet-e2e/wespeaker).
  - FluidInference/speaker-diarization-coreml (the default source's CoreML
    conversion): SDK Apache-2.0; parent pyannote model cc-by-4.0.
  - argmaxinc/speakerkit-coreml (the optional argmax source's conversion):
    NO declared license on the HF repo — undeclared defaults to all rights
    reserved on the converted artifact; argmax's Swift code
    (argmaxinc/argmax-oss-swift) is MIT. Enabling the argmax source in a
    distributed product means the caller assumes the licensing risk on those
    CoreML artifacts.

