────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
5. Forced-alignment model (audio::align)

audio::align pairs a CoreML wav2vec2 CTC acoustic encoder
(chordai/wav2vec2-base960h-aligner-coreml, Apache-2.0) with asry's
parity-tested alignment seam. Preserve the chordai Apache-2.0 notice when
redistributing the encoder weights.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
6. CLAP audio + text encoders and bundled tokenizer (embeddings::clap)

embeddings::clap runs CoreML conversions of LAION's `clap-htsat-unfused` audio
and text encoders, and BUNDLES the Xenova CLAP tokenizer into the compiled crate
via `include_bytes!` (exposed as `coremlit::embeddings::clap::BUNDLED_TOKENIZER`).

  6a) Encoder weights — LAION CLAP (clap-htsat-unfused). The crate ships NO model
      files; it loads FinDIT-Studio's CoreML conversion, a derivative work of the
      LAION weights.

        Original model: laion/clap-htsat-unfused
        https://huggingface.co/laion/clap-htsat-unfused
        Snapshot revision: 8fa0f1c6d0433df6e97c127f64b2a1d6c0dcda8a
        License: CC-BY-4.0 — REQUIRES attribution when redistributing the weights
        (or a binary bundling them).
        Attribution: LAION (Large-scale Artificial Intelligence Open Network) —
        CLAP (Contrastive Language-Audio Pretraining), "Large-scale Contrastive
        Language-Audio Pretraining with Feature Fusion and Keyword-to-Caption
        Augmentation" (Wu et al., ICASSP 2023).

        CoreML conversion actually loaded: FinDIT-Studio/clapkit-coreml
        https://huggingface.co/FinDIT-Studio/clapkit-coreml
        fp16 revision 97d631f3814e1e46b798a8e88c9aa2e2202fdf67; int8 revision
        02a99c6a. Per-file SHA-256 pinned in tests/clap/model_io.rs and
        tests/clap/text_model_io.rs.

      License note. Attribution to `laion/clap-htsat-unfused` is provided as
      required. textclap's models/MODELS.md treats the LAION CLAP checkpoints as
      CC-BY-4.0; the current upstream Hugging Face card declares apache-2.0. Both
      require attribution, which this record provides; a downstream redistributor
      should honor whichever the upstream author intends.

  6b) Bundled tokenizer — Xenova clap-htsat-unfused (via include_bytes!).
      Compiled into the crate, so any binary linking coremlit with the `clap`
      feature redistributes it.

        Source: https://huggingface.co/Xenova/clap-htsat-unfused
        Revision (commit SHA): c28f2883575e590e04d3146ff0713c2448d691ba
        Artifact: tokenizer.json
        SHA-256: dc239041d98de27ffc3975473a1a23e3db4c937b23c138c38bbc66588bd247e5

      The artifact is the CLAP tokenizer configuration and vocabulary/merges —
      the RoBERTa (roberta-base, MIT lineage) tokenizer as packaged for the
      transformers.js / ONNX export; it carries no model weights. A redistributor
      should honor the upstream Xenova export's terms and the RoBERTa tokenizer's
      MIT license for the configuration.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
7. granite text-embedding encoder and bundled tokenizer (embeddings::granite)

embeddings::granite runs a CoreML conversion of IBM's
`granite-embedding-97m-multilingual-r2` text encoder (a ModernBERT encoder with
CLS pooling, 384-dim), and BUNDLES that model's tokenizer into the compiled
crate via `include_bytes!` (exposed as
`coremlit::embeddings::granite::BUNDLED_TOKENIZER`).

  7a) Encoder weights — IBM granite-embedding-97m-multilingual-r2. The crate
      ships NO model files; it loads FinDIT-Studio's CoreML conversion, a format
      conversion (no weights retrained or altered in value) of the IBM weights.

        Original model: ibm-granite/granite-embedding-97m-multilingual-r2
        https://huggingface.co/ibm-granite/granite-embedding-97m-multilingual-r2
        License: Apache-2.0 — preserve the Apache-2.0 attribution when
        redistributing the weights (or a binary bundling them).
        Attribution: IBM Granite Team, Granite Embedding models.

        CoreML conversion actually loaded: FinDIT-Studio/embedkit-coreml
        https://huggingface.co/FinDIT-Studio/embedkit-coreml
        revision 81852f70. Per-file SHA-256 pinned in tests/granite/model_io.rs.

      As an Apache-2.0 work, a redistributor must retain the license and
      copyright notices and state any changes; the CoreML conversion is a change
      of format (lowering to Apple CoreML at a fixed 512 sequence length), noted
      here.

  7b) Bundled tokenizer — granite-embedding-97m-multilingual-r2 (via
      include_bytes!). Compiled into the crate, so any binary linking coremlit
      with the `granite` feature redistributes it.

        Source: https://huggingface.co/ibm-granite/granite-embedding-97m-multilingual-r2
        Revision (commit SHA): 835ad14087e140460703cf0fae09f97d469d65c2
        Artifact: tokenizer.json
        SHA-256: 4f2842d568e2724370aec203652a42ac783c7937f8347a1a2cc7506d71f1582f

      The artifact is the granite tokenizer configuration and vocabulary/merges
      (an o200k-style BPE); it carries no model weights. It is distributed under
      the same upstream Apache-2.0 terms as the model; retain the license notice
      when redistributing it.
